    <briefdescription>
<para>Definitions and helper macros for managing driver memory-mapped input/output (MMIO) regions appropriately in either RAM or ROM. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>In most cases drivers will just want to include device.h, but including this separately may be needed for arch-level driver code which uses the DEVICE_MMIO_TOPLEVEL variants and including the main device.h would introduce header dependency loops due to that header&apos;s reliance on kernel.h. </para>
    </detaileddescription>
